1) Loaders inform webpack to take a preprocessing step for every file that includes in bundle.js 
2)install webpack using "npm i webpack"
3)babel contains 3 modules
    a) babel-loader : teaches babel how to work with webpack
    b) babel-core   : knows how to take code , parse it and generate some output files
    c) babel-preset-env : ruleset for telling babel exactly what pieces of es6/+ to look for and convert into es5
4)styles
    a)css loader : knows how to deal with css imports
    b)style-loader : take css imports and adds them to html document

(Note: remove .babelrc file for any errors and remove dependencies of no:3 and add @babel/core and @babel/preset-env )